## Phase 1: Object Detection (cuboid + tag, dual-track)

Object: cuboid 30×30×60 mm, red on 5 faces, AprilTag tag36h11 ID=3
(black-square edge ~19 mm) on one 30×30 mm face. Confirmed on hardware
2026-05-04 with dt_apriltags probe at z=200 mm (decision margin 63.1).

### 1.1 Cube specification — DONE 2026-05-04
- [x] Shape, dimensions, color, tag family/ID/size all confirmed.
- [x] Lighting: indoor LED overhead, blinds drawn, minimal shadows.

### 1.2 Detection pipeline (dual-track)
- [ ] **Track A — AprilTag (preferred when tag face visible)**: dt_apriltags
      detector for tag36h11 ID=3 on `/camera/color/image_raw` → full 6-DOF
      pose. Confidence high.
- [ ] **Track B — HSV red segmentation (always-on fallback)**:
  - [ ] BGR → HSV conversion
  - [ ] HSV threshold tuning via interactive trackbar tool (`hsv_tuner.py`)
  - [ ] Morphological open/close
  - [ ] Contour extraction + area + aspect-ratio filter (cuboid is 1:2)
  - [ ] Centroid depth-lift via `/camera/depth/image_raw` + intrinsics
  - [ ] Yaw inferred from contour orientation (`cv2.minAreaRect`)
  - [ ] Confidence medium
- [ ] **Priority router**: emit Track A's result if tag detected this frame,
      else emit Track B's result. Track-source recorded in output.

### 1.3 Robustness
- [ ] Test under varied lighting (LED on/off mix, partial blind open)
- [ ] Test with background clutter
- [ ] Test with partial occlusion (tag occluded → must fall to HSV; cube
      partially occluded → must still detect)
- [ ] Decide fallback: YOLOv8 if HSV unreliable in cluttered scenes

### 1.4 Detection interface
- [ ] Publish `vision_msgs/Detection3DArray` on `/cube/detections` with:
  - `bbox` (BoundingBox3D)
  - `results[0].hypothesis.class_id` ∈ {`apriltag_3`, `hsv_red`} (track source)
  - `results[0].hypothesis.score` (decision_margin/area-confidence proxy)
  - `results[0].pose.pose` in `camera_color_optical_frame`, with covariance
    encoding the per-track confidence (tag: tight; HSV: loose)
- [ ] Lock message contract; document in `Robot_info/system_architecture.md`

