## Phase 5: Object Pickup

### 5.1 Grasp pose computation
- [ ] end_effector target = cube_center + vertical offset
- [ ] Align yaw from pose estimation

### 5.2 Reachability check
- [ ] MoveIt2 IK solve before commit
- [ ] On failure: loop back to re-plan base pose

### 5.3 Pre-grasp
- [ ] Move to hover pose 5–10 cm above cube, gripper open

### 5.4 Approach
- [ ] MoveIt2 Cartesian descent

### 5.5 Close gripper
- [ ] Close to target width (not fully closed)

### 5.6 Grasp confirmation
- [ ] Check gripper effort/current feedback
- [ ] Check gripper final width vs expected cube width
- [ ] Vision re-check: cube no longer on ground
- [ ] On failure: retry or abort

### 5.7 Retreat
- [ ] Cartesian lift to safe transport height
- [ ] Tuck arm into transport pose

